overview: "The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application
  to ensure it met all acceptance criteria from the Statement of Work and a
  detailed questionnaire specification. The agent conducted a thorough analysis,
  identifying both well-implemented features and significant gaps. Following
  this review, the agent proceeded to implement three high-priority missing
  features: a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference, including critical
  safety warnings for high scores; the detection and detailed reporting of
  Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA); and the detection and
  recommendation for Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. These changes involved
  updating data types, validation rules, user interface components, and both the
  web-based and PDF report generation logic to provide comprehensive feedback to
  the user."
